Path: README.md
 1	# Socket Server with Thread Pool
 2	
 3	A Java-based multi-threaded socket server implementation that demonstrates concurrent client handling using a thread pool architecture. This project provides a robust server solution with graceful shutdown capabilities and administrative monitoring.
 4	
 5	## Features
 6	
 7	- **Thread Pool Architecture**: Efficiently handles multiple concurrent client connections using a fixed-size thread pool
 8	- **HTTP Response Support**: Returns proper HTTP responses to client requests
 9	- **Graceful Shutdown**: Administrative interface for controlled server shutdown
 10	- **Status Monitoring**: Real-time server status checking capabilities
 11	- **Console Management**: Interactive command-line interface for server administration
 12	- **Thread-Safe Operations**: Uses atomic operations for safe concurrent access
 13	
 14	## Project Structure
 15	
 16	```
 17	src/main/java/dev/mars/
 18	 StartStop.java # Main application entry point
 19	 ThreadPooledServer.java # Core server implementation
 20	 WorkerRunnable.java # Client request handler
 21	 ShutdownMonitor.java # Administrative monitoring service
 22	```
 23	
 24	## Architecture Overview
 25	
 26	### Core Components
 27	
 28	1. **ThreadPooledServer**: The main server that listens for client connections on port 9000
 29	 - Uses a fixed thread pool (default: 10 threads)
 30	 - Accepts incoming socket connections
 31	 - Delegates client handling to worker threads
 32	
 33	2. **WorkerRunnable**: Handles individual client requests
 34	 - Processes each client connection in a separate thread
 35	 - Returns HTTP-compliant responses
 36	 - Logs request processing details
 37	
 38	3. **ShutdownMonitor**: Administrative service running on port 9001
 39	 - Provides server status checking
 40	 - Enables graceful server shutdown
 41	 - Accepts administrative commands
 42	
 43	4. **StartStop**: Main application launcher
 44	 - Initializes and starts both servers
 45	 - Provides console-based command interface
 46	 - Manages application lifecycle
 47	
 48	## Technical Specifications
 49	
 50	- **Java Version**: 24
 51	- **Build Tool**: Maven
 52	- **Main Server Port**: 9000
 53	- **Admin Port**: 9001
 54	- **Default Thread Pool Size**: 10 threads
 55	- **Response Format**: HTTP/1.1 with proper headers
 56	
 57	## Getting Started
 58	
 59	### Prerequisites
 60	
 61	- Java 24 or higher
 62	- Maven 3.6+
 63	
 64	### Building the Project
 65	
 66	```bash
 67	mvn clean compile
 68	```
 69	
 70	### Running the Server
 71	
 72	```bash
 73	mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="dev.mars.StartStop"
 74	```
 75	
 76	Or compile and run directly:
 77	
 78	```bash
 79	javac -cp src/main/java src/main/java/dev/mars/*.java
 80	java -cp src/main/java dev.mars.StartStop
 81	```
 82	
 83	## Usage
 84	
 85	### Starting the Server
 86	
 87	When you run the application, it will:
 88	
 89	1. Start the main server on port 9000
 90	2. Start the shutdown monitor on port 9001
 91	3. Display a console prompt for commands
 92	
 93	### Console Commands
 94	
 95	The application provides an interactive console with the following commands:
 96	
 97	- `status` - Check if the server is running
 98	- `shutdown` - Gracefully shutdown the server
 99	- `quit` - Exit the console application
 100	
 101	### Testing the Server
 102	
 103	#### Test Client Connections
 104	
 105	You can test the server using various tools:
 106	
 107	**Using curl:**
 108	```bash
 109	curl http://localhost:9000
 110	```
 111	
 112	**Using telnet:**
 113	```bash
 114	telnet localhost 9000
 115	```
 116	
 117	**Using netcat:**
 118	```bash
 119	echo "GET / HTTP/1.1" | nc localhost 9000
 120	```
 121	
 122	#### Administrative Commands
 123	
 124	**Check server status:**
 125	```bash
 126	echo "status" | nc localhost 9001
 127	```
 128	
 129	**Shutdown server:**
 130	```bash
 131	echo "shutdown" | nc localhost 9001
 132	```
 133	
 134	## Server Response
 135	
 136	The server returns HTTP-compliant responses in the following format:
 137	
 138	```
 139	HTTP/1.1 200 OK
 140	Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
 141	Content-Length: [length]
 142	
 143	WorkerRunnable: ThreadPooledServer - [timestamp]
 144	```
 145	
 146	## Configuration
 147	
 148	### Customizing Server Settings
 149	
 150	You can modify the server configuration by editing the `StartStop.java` file:
 151	
 152	```java
 153	// Change port and thread pool size
 154	var threadPooledServer = new ThreadPooledServer(9000, 10); // port, thread count
 155	var shutdownMonitor = new ShutdownMonitor(9001, threadPooledServer); // admin port
 156	```
 157	
 158	### Thread Pool Sizing
 159	
 160	The default thread pool size is 10. Consider adjusting based on:
 161	- Expected concurrent connections
 162	- Server hardware capabilities
 163	- Response time requirements
 164	
 165	## Thread Safety
 166	
 167	The implementation uses several thread-safety mechanisms:
 168	
 169	- `AtomicBoolean` for server state management
 170	- `synchronized` methods for critical sections
 171	- Thread-safe `ExecutorService` for task management
 172	- Proper resource cleanup with try-with-resources
 173	
 174	## Logging
 175	
 176	The server provides comprehensive logging:
 177	
 178	- Client connection notifications
 179	- Request processing timestamps
 180	- Thread identification for debugging
 181	- Error handling with stack traces
 182	- Server lifecycle events
 183	
 184	## Lifecycle Management
 185	
 186	### Server Startup
 187	1. Initialize thread pool
 188	2. Bind to server socket
 189	3. Start accepting connections
 190	4. Launch shutdown monitor
 191	
 192	### Request Processing
 193	1. Accept client connection
 194	2. Submit to thread pool
 195	3. Process in worker thread
 196	4. Return HTTP response
 197	5. Close client socket
 198	
 199	### Server Shutdown
 200	1. Stop accepting new connections
 201	2. Complete existing requests
 202	3. Shutdown thread pool
 203	4. Close server socket
 204	5. Clean up resources
 205	
 206	## Contributing
 207	
 208	This project serves as an educational example of socket programming and thread pool management in Java. Feel free to extend it with additional features such as:
 209	
 210	- SSL/TLS support
 211	- Request routing
 212	- Session management
 213	- Performance metrics
 214	- Configuration files
 215	
 216	## License
 217	
 218	This project is provided as-is for educational purposes.
